{"title": "On Liberty (Version 2)", "description": "On Liberty by John Stuart Mill is an essay about individual freedom and its limits. Mill argues that people should be free to think, speak, and act as they wish, as long as they don\u2019t harm others. He believes this freedom leads to progress and happiness. Governments and society shouldn\u2019t control people\u2019s choices unless those choices hurt someone else. On Liberty is pertinent to contemporary debates about free speech, personal rights, and social control and so retains its relevance, perhaps more urgently than ever. Mill\u2019s work is key to a proper understanding of the balance between freedom and responsibility, in a world where the exercise of power and the use of new technologies threaten liberty around the world. (Summary by Bryn Roberts)", "duration": 23135, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "2881", "name": "John Stuart Mill"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/onliberty_2505_librivox/on_liberty_2505.jpg", "copyright_year": "1901", "genres": ["Political Science"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "Bryn Roberts"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Bryn Roberts"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "J. M. Smallheer"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "mleigh"}], "sections": [{"section": 0, "title": "Introduction", "readers": [18007], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/onliberty_2505_librivox/onliberty_00_mill_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1900}, {"section": 1, "title": "Chapter 1 Pt 1", "readers": [18007], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/onliberty_2505_librivox/onliberty_01_mill_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1232}, {"section": 2, "title": "Chapter 1 Pt 2", "readers": [18007], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/onliberty_2505_librivox/onliberty_02_mill_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1439}, {"section": 3, "title": "Chapter 2 Pt 1", "readers": [18007], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/onliberty_2505_librivox/onliberty_03_mill_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1533},